━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[!!]  Implement mTLS between internal Docker services
      → warden ↔ app ↔ analytics ↔ postgres
      → Use Docker Swarm secrets or Vault for cert distribution

[!!]  Add API key authentication on POST /filter
      → Keys stored hashed in warden_core.api_keys (table already in init.sql)
      → FastAPI dependency: extract X-API-Key header, validate against DB
      → Return 401 on missing/invalid key

[!!]  Add rate limiting per API key on POST /filter
      → Suggested: slowapi (Starlette-compatible) + Redis back-end
      → Limits: 100 req/min per key, 10 000 req/day per key (configurable)
      → Return 429 with Retry-After header on exceed

[!!]  Harden Nginx configuration
      → Add security headers: HSTS, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options
      → Restrict /dashboard/ to internal network or VPN IP range in prod
      → Disable server_tokens (already done — verify)

[!]   Run warden container as non-root user
      → Add USER warden (uid 1000) to warden/Dockerfile
      → Adjust /warden/data volume permissions accordingly

[!]   Implement Playwright sandbox resource limits
      → Cap CPU and memory per browser context in tools/browser.py
      → Add request timeout and max-response-size guards

[!]   Add Content Security Policy header on dashboard Nginx route

[!]   Document API key rotation procedure in README

