  5. PERFORMANCE & SCALABILITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[!]   Pre-warm MiniLM model on container startup
      → Embed a single dummy sentence in the lifespan() handler
      → Eliminates 100–300 ms cold-start penalty on first real request

[!]   Cache frequently seen content hashes in Redis
      → Skip full pipeline for exact duplicate payloads (replay protection)
      → TTL: 5 minutes; key = sha256(content)

[!]   Benchmark SemanticGuard corpus scaling
      → Profile cosine similarity at 100 / 500 / 1000 / 5000 examples
      → If > 500 examples causes > 50 ms overhead, consider FAISS index

[!]   Add horizontal scaling documentation
      → warden service is stateless except for in-process corpus cache
      → Document: SemanticGuard.add_examples() only updates one replica
      → Fix: load dynamic_rules.json from shared Redis on startup

[ ]   Add GPU support path (optional)
      → Detect CUDA availability at startup, use GPU embeddings if present
      → Keep CPU-only as default; document GPU activation in README

[ ]   Investigate async embedding for non-blocking ML inference
      → Move embedding call to a ThreadPoolExecutor
      → Prevents FastAPI worker thread from blocking on numpy operations

